text:
Tuesday, 21 February 2017 | MYT 7:48 PM Yang di-Pertuan Agong presents letters of credence to 10 diplomats Yang di-Pertuan Agong Sultan Muhammad V (centre) with Malaysian heads of mission at Istana Negara 
KUALA LUMPUR: The Yang di-Pertuan Agong Sultan Muhammad V presented letters of credence to 10 new Malaysian heads of mission at Istana Negara today. 
They are Zainal Abidin Bakar who will be the new ambassador to Spain and Syed Hasrin Tengku Hussin who is the new envoy to United Arab Emirates. 
Datuk Rustam Yahaya who is going to Iran was the Undersecretary of Americas prior to his appointment while Cheong Loon Lai who had served as the High Commissioner to Ghana will head to Hungary. 
The other envoys who received their letters were Datuk Hidayat Abdul Hamid (India) Siti Hajjar Adnin (Ireland), Mohd Aini Atan (Laos), Syed Mohamad Bakri Syed Abdul Rahman (Kazakhstan), Datuk Mohd Khalid Abbasi Abdul Razak (Argentina) and Agus Salim Yusof (Bahrain).
